title: Oct. 3: Mount Saint Mary roundup
text: Posted Oct. 4, 2015 at 2:00 AM Posted Oct. 4, 2015 at 2:00 AM » Social News Men's cross country George Mason Invitational Team scores: 1. George Mason 22 points; 2. Virginia Military Institute 33; 3. Mount Saint Mary 85; 4. Brooklyn 120. Scott Baker led Mount St. Mary’s, finishing 27th with 27:04.93 at Oatlands Plantation in Leesburg, Va. Benjamin Finnegan was the Mountaineers’ next-best finisher, taking 30th with 27:20.45. Women's cross country George Mason Invitational Team scores: 1. George Mason 15; 2. Virginia Tech 55; 3. Virginia Military Institute 71; Mount Saint Mary 94; Brooklyn 135. Ashleigh Kocher was the top Mount St. Mary’s finisher, placing 20th with 25:16.89 at Oatlands Plantation in Leesburg, Va. Mary Funk finished 23rd with 25:33. Men's soccer Mount Saint Mary 3, Sarah Lawrence 0 Joey Dolan scored in the 23th minute (Connor Lynch assist), Bekeret Watts scored in the 32nd (Lynch, Michael Blaauboer assist) and Dolan scored again in the 60th for the Mountaineers. Mount Saint Mary is 4-7-1, 3-1 in the Skyline Conference. recordonline.com
